The National Directorate of Employment (NDE) has commenced a three-month skills training for 34 unemployed graduates in Plateau State under a programme called Advanced National Open Apprenticeship Scheme (A-NOAS). The participants, according to NDE, who were drawn from the 17 local government areas of the state, would be trained on advanced beauty therapy, fashion design, computer application and catering. The acting Director General (DG) of NDE, Malam Abubakar Nuhu Fikpo, represented by Malam Yusuf Umar, while congratulating the participants during their orientation, urged them to take the training seriously.